<head3>(Auto Resize Terminal\ar_terminal)
<p>
Changing the window size does not usually change the
size of the DECterm display area.
Clicking on Auto Resize Terminal causes the display area
to match the window size.
   


<head3>(Auto Resize Window\ar_window)
<p>
Changing the size of the DECterm display area (the number
of rows and columns) usually changes the window size automatically.
Clicking on Auto Resize Window lets you change the size of
the DECterm display without changing the window size.
If the display area is larger than the window, information is
not visible. Use scroll bars to access areas outside the window
boundary.
         
   
<head3>(Terminal Driver Resize\td_resize)

<p>
When you modify the terminal driver the 
size of DECterm also changes.  Clicking on Terminal Driver Resize
disables this option.


<head3>(Big Font\big_font)

<p>

Clicking on the Big Font option
causes DECterm to display an 18-point font.
By default, DECterm displays a 14-point font.
                     
<head3>(Default Big Font\big_default)

<p>
When "Default" is selected, DECterm will use a standard DECterm 18 point
font.  This will override the use of the font name supplied in the text
entry field adjacent to the "Other" button.

<head3>(Other Big Font\big_other)

<p>
When "Other" is selected, DECterm will attempt to use the font specified in
the adjacent text entry field.


<head3>(Other Big Font Name\big_text)

<p>
The font name field is used to enter the name of a font for DECterm to
use instead of the default font.  To use the font entered in this field,
select the "Other" button next to it.

<p>
Note: Not all DECterm features will work properly with all fonts, for
example double-height characters, bold characters, technical character set
characters, etc.



<head3>(Little Font\little_font)

<p>
By default, DECterm displays a 14-point font.
Clicking on the Big Font option
causes DECterm to display an 18-point font.

<head3>(Default Little Font\little_default)

<p>
When "Default" is selected, DECterm will use a standard DECterm 14 point
font.  This will override the use of the font name supplied in the text
entry field adjacent to the "Other" button.

<head3>(Other Little Font\little_other)

<p>
When "Other" is selected, DECterm will attempt to use the font specified in
the adjacent text entry field.


<head3>(Other Little Font Name\little_text)

<p>
The font name field is used to enter the name of a font for DECterm to
use instead of the default font.  To use the font entered in this field,
select the "Other" button next to it.

<p>
Note: Not all DECterm features will work properly with all fonts, for
example double-height characters, bold characters, technical character set
characters, etc.



<head3>(German Standard Font\gs_font)

<p>

 Clicking on German Standard Font causes DECterm to use
 a font that meets the German Technical Supervision Association (TÜV)
 requirements.
<p>
 This font cannot be condensed.
   

<head3>(Default German Standard Font\gs_default)

<p>
When "Default" is selected, DECterm will use the German Standard font.  This
will override the use of the font name supplied in the text entry field
adjacent to the "Other" button.

<head3>(Other German Standard Font\gs_other)

<p>
When "Other" is selected, DECterm will attempt to use the font specified in
the adjacent text entry field.


<head3>(Other German Standard Font Name\gs_text)

<p>
The font name field is used to enter the name of a font for DECterm to
use instead of the default font.  To use the font entered in this field,
select the "Other" button next to it.

<p>
Note: Not all DECterm features will work properly with all fonts, for
example double-height characters, bold characters, technical character set
characters, etc.


<head3>(Normal Font (80 Columns)\normal_font)

<P>

Clicking on the Normal Font (80 Columns) option causes the 80 column font
to be used, regardless of the number of columns.
The default option is Normal Font/80,
Condensed/132.
<p>
This setting is always used if the German Standard Font option is selected.
    
<head3>(Condensed Font (132 Columns)\condensed_font)

<p>
Clicking on the Condensed Font (132 Columns)
 option causes a condensed font to be used, regardless of
the number of columns.  The default font size is Normal/80, 
Condensed/132.
<p>
This setting has no effect if the German Standard Font
option is selected.
    
<head3>(Normal/80, Condensed/132\variable_font)

<p>
The default font size is Normal/80, Condensed/132.
This option causes the font size to adjust to match the terminal width.
The normal font is used for 80 columns or less; the 
condensed font is used for more than 80 columns.
<p>

This setting has no effect if the German Standard Font option is selected.
  
<head3>(Window Title\window_title)

<p>
Entering a title of your choice in the text entry box 
changes the name in the title bar.




<head3>(Icon Name\icon_name)

<p>
Entering a title of 
your choice in the text entry box changes the name in the icon.


                                                                   
<head3>(Terminal Size\terminal_size)


<p>


By default, the size of DECterm is 24 rows and 80 columns.
You can change the size
by clicking on one of the displayed default sizes.
You can also set the column and row to be any
number from 1 to 132 by clicking on the text entry box, deleting any existing
numbers, and entering the new settings.

    



<head3>(Rows\rows)

<P>

The size of DECterm is 24 rows and 80 columns by default.
You can set the rows to be any
number from 1 to 132 by clicking on the text entry box, deleting any existing
numbers, and entering the new settings.

<head3>(24 Rows\rows_24)

<P>
The default terminal size is 24 rows and 80 columns.  



<head3>(48 Rows\rows_48)

<P>

Click on 48 to change the the setting to 48 rows.


<head3>(72 Rows\rows_72)

<P>
Click on 72 to change the setting to 72 rows.


<head3>(Columns\columns)

<P>

The default DECterm size is 24 rows and 80 columns.  
You can also set the columns to be any
number from 1 to 132 by clicking on the text entry box, deleting any existing
numbers, and entering the new settings.




<head3>(80 Columns\columns_80)

<P>
The default DECterm size is 24 rows and 80 columns.

<head3>(132 Columns\columns_132)

<P>

Click on 132 to change the setting to 132 columns.



