<head3>(Numeric Keypad\numeric_keypad)

<p> 

The default numeric keypad displays the character that
appears on the numeric key that you press.

<head3>(Application Keypad\appl_keypad)

<p>

Choose the application keypad by clicking on the
Application Keypad option.  This causes user-defined characters
to be displayed.
                     

<head3>(UPSS DEC Supplemental\upss_mcs) 

<p>
The UPSS DEC Supplemental option is
the default that causes the DEC Multinational Character Set to be used.
<p>              


<head3>(UPSS ISO Latin 1\upss_latin_1)

<p>You can change the default character set 
by
clicking on the UPSS ISO Latin 1 option.  This causes the
International Standards Organization (ISO) Latin 1 Character Set to be used.      
To use this character set,  the Character Set mode option must be
set to 8-Bit Characters.

<condition>(turkish)
<head3>(UPSS DEC Turkish Supplemental\upss_dec_turkish)

<p>
The UPSS DEC Turkish Supplemental option is
the default that causes the DEC Turkish Supplemental Character Set to be used.

<head3>(UPSS ISO Latin 5\upss_iso_turkish)

<p>You can change the default character set 
by
clicking on the UPSS ISO Latin 5 option.  This causes the
International Standards Organization (ISO) Latin 5 Character Set to be used.      
To use this character set,  the Character Set mode option must be
set to 8-Bit Characters.
<endcondition>


<condition>(greek)
<head3>(UPSS DEC Greek Supplemental\upss_dec_greek)

<p>You can change the default character set 
by
clicking on the UPSS DEC Greek Supplemental option.  This causes the
DEC Greek Supplemental Character Set to be used.      
<endcondition>


<head3>(8-Bit Multinational Characters\eight_bit)

<p>
The default character
mode is set to 8 bits for use with either the DEC Supplemental  
or the ISO Latin 1 Supplemental
Character Set.

<head3>(7-Bit NRCS Characters\seven_bit)

<p>

To use National Replacement Character Sets, click on the 
7-Bit NRCS Character
Mode option.  This option lets DECterm operate
in 7-bit mode, using the national character replacement set selected
in the 7-Bit NRCS dialog box.
The default is the 8-Bit Multinational Character Set.

<head3>(Answerback Message\answerback_message)
<p>
Any text entered into this field will be sent to the host when DECterm
is requested by the host to send its answerback message or when the user
hits CTRL-F5.

<head3>(Conceal Answerback Message\conceal_answerback)

<p>

When this button is selected, the answerback message entered into the
"Answerback Message" text entry field will not be displayed in the dialog
box.

<p>
Once selected, this button cannot be deselected.  The only way to
deselect it, is to select the "Answerback Message" text entry field, which
will erase the previous answerback message.
 


<head3>(VT300 Mode, 8-Bit Controls\vt300_8_bit)

<p>

By default, DECterm emulates a VT300-series terminal with
7-bit control characters (codes 0-31).  You can change the 
mode to
VT300 with 8-bit control characters by clicking on
the VT300 Mode, 8-Bit Controls option.  This causes DECterm
to translate 8-bit control characters (codes 128 to 159) for function
keys. 


<head3>(VT300 Mode, 7-Bit Controls\vt300_7_bit)

<p>

By default, DECterm operates in VT300 mode with 7-bit control
characters.  This means that function keys are transmitted
in 7-bit form.




<head3>(VT100 Mode\vt100_mode)

<p>
You can change the VT300 Mode
option by clicking on the VT100 Mode option.  This 
causes DECterm to emulate a
VT100 terminal.

<head3>(VT52 Mode\vt52_mode)

<p>

You can change the VT300 Mode, 8-Bit Controls option by
clicking on the VT52 Mode option.  This causes DECterm to emulate a
VT52 terminal.


