<head3>(Warning Bell\warning_bell)

<p>
By default, the keyboard warning bell rings when
errors occur.  Clicking on the Warning Bell option turns off the 
warning bell.        
     

<head3>(Margin Bell\margin_bell)

<p>

By default, the margin bell does not ring when the cursor reaches
the right margin.  You can cause it to ring by clicking on the Margin Bell 
option.

<head3>(F11 Key sends F11\f11_f11)
<p>
With this button enabled, DECterm reads the default F11 keyboard signal.
<head3>(F11 Key sends Escape\f11_esc)
<p>
With this button enabled, DECterm reads the F11 key as an ESC (escape)
signal.

<head3>(Auto Repeat\auto_repeat)

<p>
By default, if you press and hold a key, 
that character is displayed repeatedly.
Clicking on the Auto Repeat option causes only one character to be displayed.


<head3>(Ctrl--Q, Ctrl--S <literal>(=) Hold\ctrl_qs_hold)

<p>By default, pressing 
Ctrl + S causes the display to stop scrolling, and pressing Ctrl + Q causes the display to resume scrolling.

<condition>(osf)
<head3>(Allow QuickCopy\allow_qcopy)
<p>
With this button enabled, you can use MB2 to cut and paste text
in one step.  For this function to work, your system must be focused in
a DECterm window. Press MB2 and drag the mouse over text that you want
to cut.  The text is displayed in reverse video. Release MB2 and the
text is pasted at the current  cursor position of the DECterm window.
Notice that the text is no longer  displayed in reverse video.

<endcondition>


<head3>(Delete/Backspace Key\delete)

<p>
By default, the Delete/Backspace key functions as a delete key.

<head3>(Backspace\backspace)

<p>
You can override the Delete default by clicking on
the Backspace option.  This causes the Delete/Backspace key to function
as a nondestructive backspace key.


<head3>(Comma Key Sends <literal>(,,)\comma_comma)

<p>
On the North American and Dutch keyboards, 
the Comma Key Sends ,, option is the default.   This 
causes a comma <parendchar>(,) to be
displayed when you press the comma key, whether or not the  
key is shifted.  

                                         
<head3>(Comma Key Sends <literal>(,<)\comma_angle)
<p>                                           

On the North American and Dutch keyboards, 
you can override the Comma Key Sends ,, default by clicking on the Comma Key
Sends <literal>(,<) option.  This causes a comma <parendchar>(,)
to be displayed when you press
the comma key shifted, and a left angle bracket <parendchar>(<literal>(<)) 
to be displayed
when you press the comma key shifted.  

          
<head3>(Tilde Key Sends <literal>(`~)\tilde_tilde)

<p> 
On the North American and Dutch keyboards, 
the Tilde Key Sends `~ option is set.  
This causes
the `~ key to display a  left single quotation mark <parendchar>(`) 
when unshifted
and a tilde <parendchar>(~) when  shifted.

                                                      
<head3>(Tilde Key Sends <literal>(ESC)\tilde_esc)

<p>          

On the North American and Dutch keyboards, 
you can override the Tilde Key Sends `~ default by clicking on the Tilde Key
Sends ESC option.  This 
causes the `~ key to function as an escape (ESC) key.

                                                      
                               
<head3>(Angle Brackets Key Sends <literal>(<>)\angle_angle)

<p>

On the North American and Dutch keyboards, 
the Angle Brackets Key Sends <literal>(<>) option is set. This causes
the angle bracket key to display  a left angle bracket 
<parendchar>(<literal>(<)) when
unshifted and a right angle bracket <parendchar>(<literal>(>)) when  shifted.   


<head3>(Angle Brackets Key Sends `~\angle_tilde)
<p>

On the North American and Dutch keyboards, you 
can override the Angle Bracket Key Sends <literal>(<>) default by clicking
on the Angle Brackets Key Sends `~.  This 
causes the <literal>(<>) key to display a left single quotation mark 
<literal>(`) when unshifted and a tilde <literal>(~) when shifted. 


