<head3>(Printer Port\printer_port)

<p>
By default, the Printer Port option specifies the local printer port.  
To choose another port, enter the device name in the text entry box.

<head3>(Printer Port\port_text)

<p>
To choose a printer port, enter the device name in the text entry box.
By default, the Printer Port option specifies the local printer port.  

<head3>(File\printer_file)

<p>

By default, information printed on the screen does not
create a file.  Choosing the File option 
saves the printed output to a file.

<head3>(File\file_text)

<p>
Enter a file name to save the printed output to a file.
By default, a file is not created.

<head3>(None\printer_none)

<p>
By default, the None option discards the queued job.
   

<head3>(Normal Print Mode\normal_print)

<p>
To print characters
use the Print
   Screen key or use escape sequences.
   


<head3>(Auto Print Mode\auto_print)     


<p>
   
By default, a line of information is printed if the cursor
leaves that line because of an LF, VT, FF,  or autowrap.
   

<head3>(Printer Controller Mode\printer_controller)   


<p>

   By default, 
each character is printed as it is received.
If not selected, the character is displayed.


<head3>(Print Full Page\print_full_page)

<p>

By default, the information on the 
   display is printed not including information stored in
the transcript or status line.

<head3>(Print Full Page and Transcript\full_page_transript)

<p>
By default, the information in the transcript
   followed by the information on the display is printed.
   
<head3>(Print Scroll Region Only\print_scroll_region)

<p>
 By default, the information stored in the
   scrolling region of the display is printed.
   
 
<head3>(Print Selection Only\print_selection)

<p>
By default, the information in the
   selected region of the display and transcript is printed.


<head3>(Print National Characters Only\print_national)


<p>
By default, only national characters are printed.  Other
   characters are either converted to the corresponding national characters
or the characters are not printed.

<head3>(Print National and Line Drawing\national_line_drawing)
<p>
By default, national characters and line drawing 
characters are printed.


<head3>(Print All Characters\print_all_characters)
<p>

By default, all characters are printed, including 
multinational and technical
characters.

<head3>(Form Feed Terminator\form_feed_terminator)
<p>
By default, a FF is added at the end of each page. 
Alternately, an escape sequence can be used.

<head3>(Printer To Host\printer_to_host)
<p>
By default, any character  read on the printer port is
sent  back to the host application.  This option is available only
when the print destination is a printer port device rather 
than a print queue or a file.

<head3>(Graphics Printing\graphics_printing)

<p>
By default, graphics (bitmap) and text are printed.


<head3>(Background Printing\background_printing)
<p>
By default, the graphics background
   color is printed. Omitting 
background color saves ink and toner and maximizes printing speed.

<head3>(Level 1 Sixel Graphics\level_1_sixel)

<p>

By default, a Sixel introducer that omits the macro parameter is selected.
This option does
   not use the Sixel Set Attributes command to set the aspect ratio and the
   horizontal grid size.  As a result, the 
Sixel aspect ratio  is  2 to 1 and the 
   horizontal grid size is  approximately 188 x 0.025 mm (7.5 x 0.001
   inches).

<head3>(Level 2 Sixel Graphics\level_2_sicel)
<p>

By default, a Sixel aspect ratio of 1 to 1 
with a variable grid size is printed using 
the Sixel Set Attributes command (available with Level 2 printers).

<head3>(LA210 Sixel Graphics\la210_sixel)
<p>

By default, a Sixel introducer with the 9-macro parameter is selected.
This results in a Sixel aspect ratio of 1.02 to 1.

<head3>(Compressed Graphics Printing\compressed_printing)

<p>

By default, a compressed graphics image is printed. In Portrait mode,
the output fits on an 8 x 5 inch page.

<head3>(Expanded Graphics Printing\expanded_printing)

<p>
By default, an expanded image is printed.
In Portrait mode, the image fits on a 13-inch page.

<head3>(Rotated Graphics Printing\rotated_printing)

<p>
By default, an expanded image, rotated 90-degrees, 
is printed. The output fits on a 8 x 5 inch
page.

<head3>(Monochrome Printing\monochrome_printing)
<p>
By default, the Monochrome Printing option prints in black.

<head3>(Color Printing\color_printing)
<p>
By default, the Color Printing option prints color output.  
DECterm includes a color map 
in virtual memory to allow color printing from a monochrome system.

<head3>(HLS Color Syntax\hls_syntax)

<p>
By default, the HLS Color Syntax option specifies hue,
   lightness, and saturation (HLS).


<head3>(RGB Color Syntax\rgb_syntax)
<p>
By default, the RGB Color Syntax option selects a 
red, green, and blue (RGB) format when printed.


<head3>(7-Bit Printer Mode\printer_7bit)
<p>
When this button is selected, DECterm will modify printed text to be
compatible with printers that do not support 8-bit characters.  This
includes modifying Control Sequence Introducer strings (CSI) to use the
format Escape-Left Bracket, rather than the single 8-bit CSI character.



<head3>(8-Bit Printer Mode\printer_8bit)
<p>
When this button is selected, DECterm uses 8-bit characters when printing. 
This mode may cause problems for older printers, if they cannot interpret
8-bit characters.



