<condition>(osf)
<head3>(Secure Keyboard\secure_keyboard)
<p>

The Secure Keyboard button is included to provide a higher level of
security to your system.  With this button enabled, DECterm prevents
processes other than your own from accessing the keyboard. Also,
DECterm reverses the video of the display to denote that enhanced
security for the keyboard is enabled.

<endcondition>

<head3>(Clear Lines Off Top\clear_off_top)

<p>

You can erase information stored in the transcript by choosing the
Clear Lines Off Top option.  

<head3>(Clear Display\clear_display)

<p>
You can clear all information displayed in a DECterm 
window by choosing the Clear
Display menu item.

<head3>(Resize Window\resize_window)

<p>
Choose the Resize Window menu item to resize the 
window to match the size (number of rows and columns) of the DECterm
 display area.
   
<head3>(Clear Communications\clear_comm)
<p>
Choose the Clear Communications menu
item to reset the communications buffers.

<head3>(Reset Terminal\reset_terminal)


<p>
Clicking on Reset Terminal causes a Soft Terminal Reset (STR).
Choosing Reset Terminal also restores the default color map.


<head2>(Choosing File Options\file_entry)

<P>
Choose the File menu to access the Exit menu item and 
exit from a DECterm window. 

<head2>(Exiting\quit)

<p>
Choose Exit or enter the LOGOUT command
to exit from DECterm and close the DECterm window.




<head2>(Printing Information\print_entry)

<p>
Choose the Print menu to print information.

<p>


<P>
Additional topics:
<LIST>(UNNUMBERED)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(print_page)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(print_selected)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(print_all)
<LE><HOTSPOT>(print_graphics)
